<MELItem itemNbr="21-81-02" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-21-81-02.1.2-21-81-02_FAA">
<Title>Power Electronics Cooling System (PECS) Fluid Level Sensor Systems</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="1" maintIndicator="(M)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One may be inoperative provided: </Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Associated PECS loop fluid level is verified to be within limits every five flight days.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Associated PECS liquid ICS/SCU supply pressure sensor operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Associated PECS liquid cooling temperature sensor operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>Verify correct fluid level in associated loop every five flight days (AMM DDG 21-81-02).</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Gain access to the PECS pump package.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Connect BMS3-42 Coolant Top-Off Pack (CTOP) to reservoir top-off port.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Fill reservoir until CTOP bypasses.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Reverse CTOP flow to remove fluid.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Remove fluid based on fluid temperature per the following table:</Para>
